        "custom_liquid": "<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Barlow:wght@400;600;700;800;900&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n\n<style>\n  .faq-section {\n    background: #fff;\n    padding: 48px 16px;\n    width: 100%;\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n    font-family: 'Barlow', Arial, sans-serif;\n  }\n\n  .faq-inner {\n    max-width: 720px;\n    margin: 0 auto;\n  }\n\n  .faq-title {\n    font-size: 28px;\n    font-weight: 900;\n    color: #111;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    text-align: center;\n  }\n\n  .faq-subtitle {\n    font-size: 15px;\n    color: #666;\n    text-align: center;\n    margin-bottom: 36px;\n  }\n\n  .faq-item {\n    border-bottom: 1px solid #f0e0e5;\n  }\n\n  .faq-question {\n    width: 100%;\n    background: none;\n    border: none;\n    padding: 18px 4px;\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: space-between;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    font-size: 15px;\n    font-weight: 700;\n  }\n\n  .faq-icon {\n    width: 28px;\n    height: 28px;\n    border-radius: 50%;\n    background: #b82e38;\n    border: 2px solid #f0ccd6;\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: center;\n    color: #c0607a;\n  }\n\n  .faq-question.open .faq-icon {\n    background: #c0607a;\n    color: #fff;\n    transform: rotate(45deg);\n  }\n\n  .faq-answer {\n    max-height: 0;\n    overflow: hidden;\n    transition: 0.3s;\n  }\n\n  .faq-answer.open {\n    max-height: 300px;\n    padding-bottom: 18px;\n  }\n\n  .faq-answer p {\n    font-size: 14px;\n    color: #555;\n  }\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"faq-section\">\n  <div class=\"faq-inner\">\n\n    <h2 class=\"faq-title\">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n    <p class=\"faq-subtitle\">Everything you need to know about our posture corrector</p>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <button class=\"faq-question\" onclick=\"toggleFaq(this)\">\n        How do I use the posture corrector?\n        <span class=\"faq-icon\">+</span>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n        <p>Simply wear it like a harness and adjust the straps until it fits comfortably. It will gently pull your shoulders back to help improve your posture.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <button class=\"faq-question\" onclick=\"toggleFaq(this)\">\n        How long should I wear it each day?\n        <span class=\"faq-icon\">+</span>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n        <p>Start with 20–30 minutes per day and gradually increase the time as your body gets used to it. Consistency is key for best results.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <button class=\"faq-question\" onclick=\"toggleFaq(this)\">\n        Can I wear it under my clothes?\n        <span class=\"faq-icon\">+</span>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n        <p>Yes! It’s lightweight and discreet, so you can comfortably wear it under your clothes at work, home, or even outside.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <button class=\"faq-question\" onclick=\"toggleFaq(this)\">\n        Is it comfortable for daily use?\n        <span class=\"faq-icon\">+</span>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n        <p>The adjustable design ensures a comfortable fit for most body types. It’s made to support your posture without feeling too tight or restrictive.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <button class=\"faq-question\" onclick=\"toggleFaq(this)\">\n        Does it really help with back pain?\n        <span class=\"faq-icon\">+</span>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n        <p>It helps improve posture and reduce strain on your back and neck, which can lead to less discomfort over time with regular use.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n  function toggleFaq(btn) {\n    const answer = btn.nextElementSibling;\n    const isOpen = btn.classList.contains('open');\n\n    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-question').forEach(q => q.classList.remove('open'));\n    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-answer').forEach(a => a.classList.remove('open'));\n\n    if (!isOpen) {\n      btn.classList.add('open');\n      answer.classList.add('open');\n    }\n  }\n</script>",
